title: Sticky Clarence
description: Everything Clarence comes into contact with sticks to his body - a pen, a can of beans, even one of his chickens! Eventually, Clarence becomes the center of a big ball of objects.

title: Lonely Lonnie
description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo record themselves telling scary stories in the treehouse.

title: Clarencio Magnifico
description: Clarence performs a magic act for some of Aberdale's senior citizens.

title: Just Wait in the Car
description: As Mary runs errands, Clarence waits in the car and struggles to fight boredom.

title: Gilben's Different
description: Gilben's newly sprouted peach fuzz sparks a discussion about puberty that ultimately convinces Clarence to act more like an adult.

title: Worm Bin
description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

title: Hit the Piñata  Music Video
description: Sing along to this pinata song written by Simon Panrucker.

title: Separation Anxiety
description: After talking, passing notes and throwing pencils at the ceiling in class, Ms. Baker separates Clarence and Sumo. They devise ways to communicate to each other from across the room in a series of gags.

title: Birding with Guyler
description: Guyler spends a day bird watching in Bendle Park - and makes a new special friend.

title: Big Boy
description: In order to get them to notice he's more mature, Clarence draws chest hairs on himself and decides to show them off!

title: Claw Machine
description: At the Pizza Swamp arcade, Clarence convinces passerby Vu to use his skills to free Clarence from the claw machine.

title: Tree of Life
description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo make it their mission to climb a really tall tree before it's set to be chopped down. As they scale higher and higher their reality begins to slip away.

title: Missing Cat
description: When Chelsea accidentally lets her pet cat Crumbles out, the cat goes missing! Reluctant to ask for help, she struggles to find the cat before anyone realizes it's gone. It's up to cat whisperer Clarence to interject and find Crumbles, whether Chelsea wants his help or not!

title: Officer Moody
description: Pieces of Mr. Reese's past are revealed when his old partner on the police force, Officer Moody, visits Aberdale Elementary.

title: Doodle Battle
description: Clarence and his pals find a large piece of paper and have fun doodling on it.

title: Belson Touch
description: After learning about King Midas' gold touch during a lesson about Greek Mythology, Clarence daydreams about having a Belson touch that turns anything he touches into Belson.

title: Percy in Have a Ball
description: Naive Percy invites his strangely quiet classmate Gilben over to play, and to show Gilben his prized ball collection.

title: Birthday
description: Jeff and Sumo expect no one to show at Clarence's birthday party, just like last year. When dozens of kids arrive, the boys struggle to get face time with Clarence, the popular party host.

title: Cool Guy Clarence
description: When Clarence meets JT, the kid who mows their lawn, he finds a fast friend who shows him some cool new music, a new outlook on life and a sweet rat-tail! Clarence leans into the rat tail lifestyle, discovering a whole new side of Aberdale he never knew existed.

title: Big Trouble in Little Aberdale
description: After stumbling upon a mysterious new kid in their neighborhood , Clarence, Jeff and Sumo decide to take the kid out on the town showing him the fun of junk food, arcades and soda! However, this new lifestyle may be more then the new kid bargained for.

title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

title: Bucky and the Howl
description: After Clarence learns Sumo's in the school musical, he joins up and enthusiastically promotes the show. On opening night with a packed house, stage fright takes hold of Sumo and he runs off leaving Clarence to go on alone.

title: Rainy Day
description: Clarence and his friends play in the rain and enjoy their cozy evenings with family.

title: Dare Day
description: With Jeff on vacation, Sumo and Clarence egg each other on in a series of increasingly absurd and extreme dares. But will one of them put a stop to this dare day, before it goes too far?

title: Public Radio
description: After listening to a public radio broadcast during class, Clarence is inspired to record a radio interview of his own featuring his buddy Sumo. When Ms. Baker hears the charming interview, she calls in a favor and gets Clarence a spot on the actual Aberdale Public Radio! The search is on - to find the perfect interview subject for his big day.

title: Clarence Loves Shoopy
description: When Clarence discovers that one of his neighbors is the grumpy school recess proctor Ms. Shoop - he gets a glimpse of her home life and decides the only things she's missing are some friends. Clarence sets out on a mission to match the cranky oddball Shoop with some new pals!

title: Beans
description: Clarence attempts to wake a sleeping dog.

title: Chad and the Marathon
description: When Chad realizes his lazy habits might be rubbing off on Clarence, he decides to participate in the Aberdale Marathon. However, the athletic Chad doesn't know the first thing about being a runner, and must enlist the help of Clarence to train!

title: Beauford T. Pusser
description: Inspired by the short Every Child, an oprhan ktten is passed from kid to kid until it finally makes its way to Ms. Baker, who names him Beauford T. Pusser.
